Job-MapReduce

A generic Map Reduce job launcher.

Map/Reduce is an approach that collects data in parallel then processes data in
serial. A Map/Reduce job has 4 components/steps.

 Batch : devide the targets into batches.
 Map   : create threads to collect data from/for each batch in parallel.
 Sort  : aggregate collected data by status.
 Reduce: (optional) process aggregated data serially.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Job::MapReduce

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Job-MapReduce

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Job-MapReduce

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Job-MapReduce

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Job-MapReduce/


